@node help_main_save "Save"
@prev glo_howtouse
@next help_main_exit

  Hotkey..: s,S

  If you press this button you will save the image to the place
  entered in the textfield @{" IFF-File " LINK help_main_save} but you should know that
  you won't be informed if an existing file will be overwritten
  so be sure to specify the correct path.

@endnode

@node help_main_exit "Exit"
@prev help_main_save
@next help_main_refresh

  Hotkey..: e,E

  I think that you know what this button does, or not ?

@endnode

@node help_main_refresh "Refresh list"
@prev help_main_exit
@next help_main_hide

  Hotkey..: r,R

  If there are windows and screens which are opened after starting
  this program you can reload the list to get all screens or windows.

@endnode

@node help_main_hide "Hide window"
@prev help_main_refresh
@next help_main_mouse

  Hotkey..: d,D

  If you want to save the screen where my window appears, you
  should select this option because otherwise my program-window
  occures on the image.

@endnode

@node help_main_mouse "Actual mouse-coordinates !"
@prev help_main_hide
@next help_main_seldrawer

  Hotkey..: None

  This field shows you the actual coordinates of the mouse but
  there are different possibilities. If you've loaded the screenlist
  the coordinates depending on the screen otherwise it depends
  on the mouse ( look out for negative numbers ).

@endnode

@node help_main_seldrawer "Button to pop up an ASL-Request !"
@prev help_main_mouse
@next help_main_type

  Hotkey..: f,F

  This button pops up an ASL-Filerequester to make it easier
  to specify a destination-path. If you are selecting a file
  as a destination-path this file will be replaced by the
  image during saving-process.

@endnode

@node help_main_type "Type"
@prev help_main_seldrawer
@next help_main_left

  Hotkey..: p,P

  This cycle-gadget specifies three different types of images
  you can save:


    Screen        -  This means that the selected screen will be
                     saved. If there isn't any screen selected
                     the first screen appearing on the list will
                     be saved.

    Window        -  This means that the selected window will be
                     saved. If there isn't any window selected
                     the first window appearing on the list will
                     be saved.

    Area          -  This means that an area of a screen or a window
                     will be saved (depends on the loaded list).
                     In any case you may specify various parameters
                     for the rectangular area you want to save.

@endnode

@node help_main_left "Left"
@prev help_main_type
@next help_main_top

  Hotkey..: l,L

  The area will be specified by it's left-top-corner and it's
  dimensions. Here you can enter the distance of your area to
  the left side.

@endnode

@node help_main_top "Top"
@prev help_main_left
@next help_main_width

  Hotkey..: t,T

  The area will be specified by it's left-top-corner and it's
  dimensions. Here you can enter the distance of your area to
  the upper side.

@endnode

@node help_main_width "Width"
@prev help_main_top
@next help_main_height

  Hotkey..: w,W

  The area will be specified by it's left-top-corner and it's
  dimensions. Here you can enter the width of your area.

@endnode

@node help_main_height "Height"
@prev help_main_width
@next help_main_file

  Hotkey..: h,H

  The area will be specified by it's left-top-corner and it's
  dimensions. Here you can enter the height of your area.

@endnode

@node help_main_file "IFF-File"
@prev help_main_height
@next help_main_list

  Hotkey..: i,I

  Here you must enter the destination-path for the image-file.
  Please make sure that there is no existing file with the same
  path because in this it will be overwritten without any comment.

@endnode

@node help_main_list "Screens / Windows"
@prev help_main_file
@next glo_howtouse

  Hotkey..: None

  This list shows you all available screens or windows. You can
  switch between screens and windows by pressing the cursor-keys.

  If you've loaded the screenlist you have to press the right-key
  to switch to the windowlist.

  If you've loaded the windowlist you have to press the left-key
  to switch to the screenlist.


  Other keys:

    CURSOR UP           : moves to the entry above
    CURSOR DOWN         : moves to the entry below
  
    CUSOR UP    + SHIFT : moves to the top of the page
    CUSOR DOWN  + SHIFT : moves to the bottom of the page

    CURSOR UP   + CTRL  : moves to the first entry
    CURSOR DOWN + CTRL  : moves to the last entry

@endnode
